Governor David Umahi of Ebonyi State, on Thursday, warned that he would sack any appointee who criticises President Muhammadu Buhari. This was contained in a statement his Special Assistant on New Media, Mr. Francis Nwaze. It said Umahi “has prohibited any of his political appointees from castigating or abusing the Nigerian President, Gen. Muhammadu Buhari. “Doing such to any government or any Governor in this country has no value to add to his administration. “The Governor has advised that anyone who wishes to throw unnecessary stone against any of the above mentioned leaders, should, in his or her own best interest, get ready to leave his government as such will attract immediate sack. “Any posting, henceforth against the President, any Governor or government from any of his appointees will attract immediate termination of appointment by him. “If you want to castigate the President, his government or any Governor, you must leave Governor Umahi government first.” Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.